I now have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me produce the complete implementation plan.

---

# Custom Theme System Implementation Plan for T3 Code

## Overview

This plan replaces the existing `"light" | "dark" | "system"` toggle with a proper multi-theme system. Three named themes ship at launch. The `resolvedTheme: "light" | "dark"` surface is preserved so all four Shiki/diff consumers continue working without changes.

---

## Step 1: `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` — Theme Data

### `ThemeColors` Interface

Every CSS variable name in `index.css` that appears in `:root` and `@variant dark` maps to a camelCase key. The new domain-specific keys (sidebar, editor, terminal, statusBar groups) are added alongside them. All values are concrete color strings — no `var()` references, because these are applied via `style.setProperty`.

```
ThemeColors {
  // Core palette — match existing :root / @variant dark names
  background: string
  foreground: string
  card: string
  cardForeground: string
  popover: string
  popoverForeground: string
  primary: string
  primaryForeground: string
  secondary: string
  secondaryForeground: string
  muted: string
  mutedForeground: string
  accent: string
  accentForeground: string
  destructive: string
  destructiveForeground: string
  border: string
  input: string
  ring: string
  info: string
  infoForeground: string
  success: string
  successForeground: string
  warning: string
  warningForeground: string

  // New domain-specific vars
  sidebarBackground: string
  sidebarForeground: string
  sidebarBorder: string
  sidebarAccent: string
  sidebarAccentForeground: string
  sidebarRing: string

  editorBackground: string
  editorForeground: string
  editorBorder: string

  terminalBackground: string
  terminalForeground: string

  statusBarBackground: string
  statusBarForeground: string
}
```

### CSS variable name mapping (camelCase → kebab-case)

The TypeScript key maps to the CSS custom property via a simple transform: `camelCase → kebab-case`. For example:
- `cardForeground` → `--card-foreground`
- `sidebarBackground` → `--sidebar-background`
- `editorBackground` → `--editor-background`
- `terminalBackground` → `--terminal-background`
- `statusBarBackground` → `--status-bar-background`

This transform should be implemented as a helper in `theme.ts`:

```ts
function toKebab(key: string): string {
  return key.replace(/([A-Z])/g, (c) => `-${c.toLowerCase()}`);
}

export function themeColorsToCssVars(colors: ThemeColors): Record<string, string> {
  return Object.fromEntries(
    Object.entries(colors).map(([key, value]) => [`--${toKebab(key)}`, value])
  );
}
```

### `Theme` and `ThemeId` Types

```ts
export type ThemeId = "t3-dark" | "t3-light" | "t3-midnight";

export interface Theme {
  id: ThemeId;
  label: string;
  isDark: boolean;
  colors: ThemeColors;
}

export const THEMES: Record<ThemeId, Theme> = { ... };
export const THEME_IDS: readonly ThemeId[] = ["t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight"];
export const DEFAULT_THEME_ID: ThemeId = "t3-dark";

export function isThemeId(value: unknown): value is ThemeId {
  return typeof value === "string" && value in THEMES;
}
```

### Concrete Color Values

The current `index.css` uses Tailwind's built-in color tokens via `var(--color-neutral-950)` etc. Those resolve to specific hex/oklch values at build time, so we need the actual resolved values for JS application.

**`t3-light`** — matches the existing `:root` light block:
```
background:         #ffffff
foreground:         #262626   (neutral-800 ≈ #262626)
card:               #ffffff
cardForeground:     #262626
popover:            #ffffff
popoverForeground:  #262626
primary:            oklch(0.488 0.217 264)
primaryForeground:  #ffffff
secondary:          rgba(0,0,0,0.04)
secondaryForeground:#262626
muted:              rgba(0,0,0,0.04)
mutedForeground:    #737373   (neutral-500 at 90% mix ≈ #737373)
accent:             rgba(0,0,0,0.04)
accentForeground:   #262626
destructive:        #ef4444   (red-500)
destructiveForeground: #b91c1c (red-700)
border:             rgba(0,0,0,0.08)
input:              rgba(0,0,0,0.10)
ring:               oklch(0.488 0.217 264)
info:               #3b82f6   (blue-500)
infoForeground:     #1d4ed8   (blue-700)
success:            #10b981   (emerald-500)
successForeground:  #047857   (emerald-700)
warning:            #f59e0b   (amber-500)
warningForeground:  #b45309   (amber-700)
sidebarBackground:  #f5f5f5   (slightly off-white, distinct from card)
sidebarForeground:  #404040
sidebarBorder:      rgba(0,0,0,0.08)
sidebarAccent:      rgba(0,0,0,0.06)
sidebarAccentForeground: #262626
