The `:root` block currently has hardcoded CSS variable assignments referencing Tailwind built-in color tokens (`var(--color-neutral-800)` etc.). These serve as the **initial/fallback** values before JavaScript runs.

Since the `ThemeProvider` will apply theme colors via `style.setProperty` at React mount time, and the module-level `applyThemeToDOM` call in `useTheme.ts` will run synchronously on script execution (before React renders), the `:root` block can remain as-is for the fallback light values.

